name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-6.4-rc4
versionCode=202505221
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[6.4-rc4 (pre-release) -- rc4: DEVICE-VERIFIED daemon hardening (Mi A3) -- survives a corrupt/empty config (per-loop temp/capacity/voltage coercion), recovers a de-negotiated input-cut charger (apsd_rerun on resume), and coerces shutdown_capacity into the pause/resume unit domain (values below 1 still disable shutdown); uninstall keeps the acc-compat artifact and un-caps voltage/current. -- rc3: KernelSU/APatch: the acc command works on PATH without a reboot; clean uninstall restores charging and removes leftovers. Daemon engine unchanged from rc2 in rc3. rc2: field-driven fixes from the acc-compat tester. (A) DAEMON SURVIVES "no switch works": disable_charging returns 7 on total switch failure and the daemon runs under set -eu, so an unguarded call EXITED the daemon (re-enabling charging and skipping the give-up notice). The three then-body call sites are now guarded so the loop keeps retrying and reaches the runtime monitor. (B) Pixel/Tensor native-limit RESUME is now instant: native_unlatch raises charge_start_level alongside charge_stop_level=100 (stop=100 alone re-armed the FET only after 1-3 min on current firmware -- measured on Pixel 9a). (C) String-valued on/off switches are no longer dropped by the auto-detect value filter. (D) New qcom-battery/odm_battery node layout (newer Xiaomi/HyperOS) added to ctrl-files. All additive or stricter; existing configs unchanged. -- 6.4-rc1 carried: SAFETY + DIAGNOSTICS. No change to the 6.2/6.3 resume logic and no change to how charging is controlled on a working device; every change is stricter, append-only, a clamp, or diagnostic. (1) A charging switch is locked only after a SUSTAINED hold -- current is sampled 3x and a switch that stops then re-arms (e.g. MediaTek current_cmd on Xiaomi/HyperOS klee) is rejected -- in BOTH the daemon auto-locker AND the manual scanner; this stops the overcharge at its source, not after a breach. (2) The breach watchdog is gated on charger PRESENT, not online: an input-cut switch drives */online to 0 while the cable is still attached, which used to blind the watchdog on exactly those devices. (3) Out-of-range pause/resume/shutdown values now fail safe, and pause/resume are forced into one unit domain (no mixed mV/% never-pause). (4) Pure throttle nodes (step_charging, restricted_charging, cool_mode/down, system_temp_level, temp_cool) are excluded from switch candidates. (5) `acca --state` reads battery/uevent in one atomic snapshot and reports a real statusTrust (was always "unknown") plus a native-limit block for Pixel/Tensor. Plus uA/mA unit threshold unified, flip_sw on=100 re-arm, dead read-only qpnp node dropped, OPLUS charge node added. Existing configs unchanged; auto-migrate, no command.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
